# The `VPRegionBlock` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vpregionblock">VPRegionBlock</a> represents a collection of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks which form a Single-Entry-Single-Exiting subgraph of the output IR CFG. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vpregionblock">VPRegionBlock</a> represents a collection of VPBasicBlocks and VPRegionBlocks which form a Single-Entry-Single-Exiting subgraph of the output IR CFG.

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/vpregionblock">VPRegionBlock</a> may indicate that its contents are to be replicated several times. This is designed to support predicated scalarization, in which a scalar if-then code structure needs to be generated VF &#42; UF times. Having this replication indicator helps to keep a single model for multiple candidate VF&#39;s. The actual replication takes place only once the desired VF and UF have been determined.

Definition at line 3716 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/vectorize/vplan-h">VPlan.h</a>.
